title: For Sale:  MK-124 (MOD 0) Smoke and Illumination.
postcontent:
The MK-124 (MOD 0) marine smoke and illumination signal is intended for either day or night signaling by aircraft personnel downed at sea or land. The signal is a one hand operable device, intended for rescue use. One end emits orange smoke for day use; the other emits a red flare that is visible day or night. Its small size and weight permits it to be carried in life vest or flight suit pockets and on life rafts. Will ship free for two or more. PayPal available 

Application
Distress signalling for day and night use when a compact and easy to use signal is required. 

Configuration
The MK-124 MOD 0 signal consists of an aluminum cylinder fitted at each end with a protective platic cap. The flame end has three prominent heads across the face for easy nighttime identification. The cylinder is clearly labeled to provide operating instructions.

title: For Sale:  DPMS A3 Package
location: St. Tammany Parish, New Orleans, Louisiana
postcontent:
I'm here today to put up for sale my DPMS A3 Classic. It's a 20" 1:9 twist HBAR chambered for 5.56/.223 and A2 stock.

The rifle itself has had roughly 300 rounds through it that consisted of nothing but factory new Federal 55gr M193 or 62gr M855. Cleaned after each range trip, it is functionally flawless. Zero issues with it and pleasantly accurate. I've taken it to Honey Island range several times for the 100 yard range and have hit the gong consistently with this rifle. If you've been hesitant about a DPMS, let this ad change your mind. I was truly amazed with this rifle.

So why am I getting rid of it? Simple, I just want to try something different. I've had my fun with it and with the holidays right around the corner no doubt someone would be very happy to receive this on Christmas Morning! Or on one of the days of Hanukkah, or whatever you celebrate, even Festivus!

It does have some obvious signs of wear and use, which you can view in the pictures. Though they are nothing major, they can be easily fixed with a bluing pen and some elbow grease. Then again this rifle is meant to be shot and handled, not left in the safe for the occasional looksie. The flattop upper receiver allows the rifle to be optics ready or whatever sight fancies your taste.

Well by now you're probably asking what makes this a package? This is where it gets fun!

Purchase of this rifle includes the following (all which can be seen in photos below):
- Rifle bag
- 3 point sling
- Not one, not two, not three but FOUR magazines! Three 30 round standard mags and... wait for it... a 20 round COLT magazine!
- Knight's Armament M5 RAS, that's right the same rail system used by the United States Marine Corps on their M16A4s! It's a two piece drop in and comes with one rail cover!
- And just when you think that was it, I'm throwing in a BSA mildot scope ready for a scope mount of your choice to go on the rifle!

All totaled the value of this package exceeds $1,000 for everything included. I'm starting the offer at $900. Make this the ultimate gift for that love one of yours and make it a memorable holiday season with such an epic deal with great items!

I'm currently not entertaining any trades of any kind so please don't bother. My price is somewhat firm. I can negotiate some but please no low ball offers. I know what this is worth and it's not just the gun you're buying. I am not splitting anything up or selling the rifle separately unless you're willing to pay $700 for the rifle alone with one mag. Other than that the package stands as is.

Feel free to send me a message for info, pics, or to make an offer. Low balls and trade offers will not be entertained.

And now for the pictures!

title: For Sale:  Finnish M39 SKY Mosin Nagant Beautiful
postcontent:
Please read the entire listing.  I am selling a beautiful 1942 Sk.Y Finnish M39 Mosin Nagant. The Finnish M39's have a reputation for being some of the nicest, most accurate Mosins, with a fascinating history.  This is one of 10,000 Sk.Y rifles issued to the Finnish Home Guard to fight the Russians.  The Finns captured these rifles from Russians, and after rebarreling, restocking and improving the sights, used them against their original owners.  The tiger stripe Beech stock on this rifle is beautiful, and all of the metal has a nice, shiny grey patina.  Stock is cleaned, no cosmoline, and treated with Tom's 1/3 mix.  The bore is good, and there is a small, discrete import mark on the bottom of the barrel just behind the front sight.  The stock appears to have been sanded at some point in its life, as the SAKO cartouche on the stock is not intact and barely visible. This SAKO example was built on an 1898 Tula receiver, as as such, does not need to go through an FFL.

I have a fairly new Arsenal SAM7SF. This is a Bulgarian AK-47 that is milled and has a right-siding folding stock. I have shot roughly 200 rounds down the barrel and is most definitely the nicest AK-47 I have ever held or shot. The rifle comes with Bulgarian bakelite handguards, the polymer heatshield handguards, Bulgarian AK sling, ten 30 round magazines (Yugo and various others), roughly 1,000 rounds of Tula 7.62x39, a soft case, and a case for the ammo. If you do some research on this amazing rifle you will find that it is one of the best made AK's on the market today. Below are some more details from the K-VAR site.

This 7.62x39 caliber rifle combines authentic, high-quality features rarely seen in the American market. From its unique right-side folding tubular buttstock to its 24x1.5mm muzzle threads with muzzle brake, every component of the SAM7SF is engineered to provide decades of dependable and accurate service. The SAM7SF rifle is bound to become a sought-after shooter and collectible firearm.

Arsenalâ€™s Exclusive Milled And Forged Receiver
Each SAM7SF receiver is milled from a hot-die hammer forged receiver blank by the Arsenal Co. of Bulgaria.
